The paper discusses reinforcement learning algorithms, which are commonly studied in the machine learning community. The focus on adapting the trace parameter for temporal difference learning suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of function approximation and online computation also suggests that the paper may be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the practical applications of the algorithm in real-world problems suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics).
